sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K301007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Low Oxygen Level Self-induction Genetic Circuit. mNarK promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Similar to the device "Low Oxygen Level Self-induction Genetic Circuit. NarK promoter".
mNarK promoter is designed to have better affinity to activated Fnr than the NarK promoter (BBa_K239005) and hence also stronger activity under anaerobic conditions. It is also shorter than the NarK promoter (BBa_K239005).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiang Chen

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K301010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This composite part contains the self-inducing positive loop and a downstream reporter, RFP. Can be jointed with different promoters which can response to various conditions as a complete self-induction system as required.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiang Chen

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K239006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Raw genomic sequence from biocyc, Escherichia coli K-12, but modified.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence contains 2 Fnr (one of which is modified), 1 Fis, 2 NarL binding sites and initiates transcription by RNAP sigma-70. Function: Switched on during anaerobic conditions. Area of application: Detection of when the cell is switching to anaerobic metabolism.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Detect and remove possible restriction sites: XbaI, EcoRI, PstI, SpeI, AgeI, BamHI, BglII, NogMIV, NotI and XhoI. No restriction site had to be removed. Sequence starts 3 bp before the first FNR binding site and ends 6 pb after the -10 box. One pb has been changed in order optimise the first FNR binding site.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Axel Nystrom

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I13507
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Built by Josh as an intermediate in screening plasmid construction.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: jkm

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K301003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: T7 promoter is used as part of the "positive loop" for the self-inducing system in HYPOXON project. The constitutive promoter regulate the expression of the promoter activator, T7 RNA Polymerase, in order to produce the downstream product continuously.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Part was obtained by oligonucleotide synthesis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiang Chen

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K301005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: T7 RNA polymerase from the T7 genome. Used as promoter activator in our HYPOXON genetic circuit.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Adding prefix&suffix sequence in front of and after the original T7 RNAP sequence by PCR is a bit difficult.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiang Chen

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
